Zero cost, lightweight IDS appliance that can triumphantly handle small/medium business networks.  
Test LAN contains about 100 devices, ~40 connect to WAN, ~20 rely on WAN for productivity.  
Machine in question is an eMachine E-series with a single core processor and 4GB ram.  
Machine is a retired discard machine incapable of running Windows 10.  
To reduce overhead, an unused usb-to-ethernet dongle provides our monitoring interface.
To reduce the possibility of network issues, the machine's monitoring interface is accepting a port mirror of our LAN-WAN router port.
This device's only purpose in life is to provide us IDS function for emerging threats, botnet comms, and indicators of compromise.  

I began with a few other distros and cominations of packages, but quickly fell into smoothsec.  
##########################################################################################################################
### smoothsec is a lightweight snort/surricata IDS with snorby, unified2, pulledpork, pigsty, built on debian 7 wheezy ###
#####################  more info on smoothsec is available at https://github.com/smoothsec/docs/wiki  ####################
